VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'body is creating a shadow and blocking the image, but with the VR, there is no shadow. You don\'t have to put yourself into crazy positions to not block the image. Very nice. Very speedy. Awesome. The one thing I did want to try is spray'

[07:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'paint. Can I wear a respirator while also wearing the headset? When you\'re spray painting, your distance from the wall is absolutely crucial on your line width. So, is the depth perception going to throw me off? Got to try it to find'

[07:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out. Because when you do paint murals, a lot of times you don\'t have a perfectly flat wall like this. You have rough bricks, you have cinder blocks, you have all kinds of crazy surfaces. And spray paint goes great on almost anything, but'

[07:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'markers and chalk and other tracing devices don\'t work on certain surfaces. Okay, respirator on. It kind of works. Uh, okay. That\'s not'

