AUDIO: 'feature. Decrease that. You really got to you got to fuss with these controls and keep bouncing back and forth. But I am starting to get a little bit more of a hang of it. Very minutely rotate that. Oo. Okay. I think that\'s looking good.'

[09:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, let\'s see how this feels. One thing is you kind of want to keep a decent distance from the actual surface so that it doesn\'t start doing all this weird'

[10:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'optical illusion like stretching and skewing thing. All right. Yeah, this works. Honestly, not mad at this at all. Pencil works good. Definitely getting more used to my ghost hand. Getting more used to just keeping my distance away'

[10:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from the art. Not leaning in too close to try and like look closer or whatever. The one thing is when I use transfer paper, I\'m using like a colored ink on my page and it\'s pretty easy to tell where I\'ve already been. I guess I could'

[10:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reduce the opacity. Like if I want to see where I\'ve gone, I would just drop the opacity down. Okay, cool. Bring it up. Bring it down. Yeah, I could even just leave this a lot lower. Something around 39%. Now it\'s a little bit easier for me to see where I\'ve gone. And the'

[10:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ghost hand isn\'t quite as intense. So, I suppose that\'s the ticket is really reducing that opacity. The prep work on this is way quicker than transfer paper. With transfer paper, I have to prep my'

[10:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sketch. I have to make sure that it has enough contrast. Then I have to bring it as a PDF into Adobe Acrobat, print it out with the poster setting turned on, go to my printer, make sure I have the'

[11:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right amount of paper in there, print it out, cut it up, tape it together, lay down the transfer paper, tape that down, lay down my concept sketch, make sure it\'s straight, tape that down. Then I have to trace the whole thing with a ballpoint pen. And finally, my concept'

[11:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'art is transferred on there. With this, I just get my PNG in there, throw on the goggles, get it in place, and we\'re off and running. Wow. Is that it? I think that\'s all she wrote. Nice. Nice, son.'

